[h1]Nobles Auto Marry - Continued (1.1 Fix)[/h1]

A fix and continuation of [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3606305941]Nobles Auto Marry[/url] by Fart Shartley, updated to work with [b]Europa Universalis V patch 1.1.x[/b].

[h2]What it does[/h2]
Automatically pairs unmarried nobles (and optionally other estate types) for marriage each month, keeping your court populated without any manual effort. Configure eligibility rules, population limits, and notification preferences through an in-game configuration panel accessible from the Situations screen.

[h2]Fixes in this version[/h2]
[list]
[*]Updated [b]supported_game_version[/b] to [b]1.1.*[/b], eliminating the launcher incompatibility warning in 1.1.x
[*]Fixed [b]AI auto-marry[/b]: the on_actions for AI countries were defined but never wired into [i]monthly_country_pulse[/i], so the feature never fired. Now fixed.
[*]Added missing [b]hint localization keys[/b] required by the situation system (caused log spam in 1.1.x)
[*]Fixed a minor [b]localization typo[/b] (missing closing quote)
[*]Fixed [b]royal marriage reminders[/b] ignoring the "hide notifications" setting, and added a separate toggle to control them independently
[/list]

[h2]Features[/h2]
[list]
[*]Automatically marries unmarried nobles (ages 18-25) each month
[*]Three [b]eligibility modes[/b]: Unrestricted, Selective, Dynastic Preservation
[*]Optional auto-marriage for [b]Burghers, Clergy, Peasants, Dhimmi, Tribes, Cossacks[/b] estates
[*]Royal marriage reminder for crown estate characters eligible for royal marriage (independently toggleable from regular notifications)
[*][b]Population control[/b]: optionally remove surplus courtiers above a configurable limit
[*][b]AI auto-marry[/b] support (disabled by default, enable in config)
[*]Full [b]in-game configuration panel[/b] in the Situations screen
[*]Works on [b]existing saves[/b] (the situation activates within one game month)
[*]Localized in: English, French, Korean, Russian, Simplified Chinese, Turkish
[/list]

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
Pure script mod with no base game files overwritten. Compatible with most other mods. The only potential conflict is if another mod also appends to [b]monthly_country_pulse[/b] in on_action with overlapping keys.

Pairs well with [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3681583449]Marry a Local Noble - Continued[/url]. That mod lets you marry your characters to a randomly generated local noble for 25 ducats when no suitable match is available in your court.

Requires EU5 patch [b]1.1.x[/b].

[h2]Source & Contributions[/h2]
Source code is available on [url=https://github.com/JustinRudisal/nobles-auto-marry]GitHub[/url]. Pull requests and bug reports welcome.

[h2]Credits[/h2]
All credit for the concept and original implementation goes to [b]Fart Shartley[/b]. This version only adds 1.1.x compatibility and bug fixes. If the original mod is ever updated, use that instead.
